57	 * a unit radius to obtain the actual angular positions, then the minimum radius
58	 * that prevents any two adjacent mugshots from overlapping is derived from
59	 * those real positions and the y-coordinates are scaled accordingly. This is
60	 * exact — the naïve approach of dividing the node count at each depth by 2π
61	 * underestimates the required radius because the tidy-tree algorithm packs
62	 * nodes within subtree wedges, not uniformly around the full circle.
63	 *
64	 * The initial zoom scales the result to fill the available viewport height.
65	 * Hovering shows the player name in a tooltip; click to open their profile.
66	 * The chart is zoomable and pannable.
67	 *
